S. Korea to Close 13 More Overseas Missions
SEOUL , September 21 ( Xinhua ) -- South Korea will shut down 13 more overseas diplomatic missions by the end of this year to reduce spending in foreign currency , the South Korean foreign and trade ministry said Monday .
The ministry said the embassies of South Korea in Jamaica , Trinidad and Tobago , Bolivia , Yemen and Bahrain will be closed and their affairs will be taken over by missions in neighboring countries .
The nation will also close consulates general in six cities -- Karachi , Anchorage , Miami , Hagatna in Guam , Hamburg and Las Palmas while the mission to the U.N. Educational , Scientific and Cultural Organization in Paris will be merged with the South Korean embassy there .
The consulate general in Berlin will be integrated into the South Korean embassy in Bonn .
The shutdown will reduce the number of the nation 's overseas diplomatic missions to 125 by the end of this year .
In the first half of this year , South Korea closed or merged six embassies and consulates general .
The government will be able to save some 10 million U.S. dollars a year by closing or merging the missions .
South Korea has been in a serious financial crisis triggered by corporate failures and bad loans of financial institutions since late 1997 , which saw the nation 's per capita income down to 9,000 U.S. dollars from the previous year 's 10,548 U.S. dollars .
